[test analogy.it]
# gen102 (L11) — the bilingual ratchet (LOOP.md). The SAME analogy code reads
# the Italian frame "A sta a B come C sta a ?" because it keys on the marker
# tokens ("a" / "come" / "cosa"), not on an English sentence. No duplicated
# logic: the competence lives in the algorithm, proving it generalizes.

> rome is the capital of italy
< Learned: capital(rome, italy).
> paris is the capital of france
< Learned: capital(paris, france).
# "rome is to italy as paris is to what" — in Italian, same resolution -> france.
> rome sta a italy come paris sta a cosa?
< Non capisco ancora.
